{
  "stem": "365.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That was one of the cruelest and most horrible camps that I experienced in my two and a half years, almost two years and eight months that I spent in the camps, in the various camps, concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The commandant was a sadistic person.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He was a cripple with an artificial leg, from the SA.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was called the Sturm Abteilung.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were wearing the green uniforms or sometimes black uniforms, they were wearing.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were our guards.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was the commandant of them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He devised means and ways of torturing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They called that camp Erholungslager or convalescent camp, where they were sending in sick prisoners from other forced labor camps, there to recuperate.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "If it did not get back on his feet within a week to two, either he was killed on the spot or sent to a-- toa a extermination camp, like to Auschwitz or somewhere else, where he gassed.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Others that were extremely sick, they were killed there in Brande, right on spot.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They were killed by means of a cold shower.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Now, I don't know if you can imagine killing a person just by giving him a cold shower.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It's very simple.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "If the person is tied down, he's sick, weak like he is, and you put a steam of cold water on him, his lungs collapse.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And he actually suffocates, grasping for breaths-- maximum, five minutes, less, and he's dead.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But it's a horrendous death.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Those are the means that they was killing the people by.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Number two, every Sunday, that was an entertainment for him to make what he called [NON-ENGLISH] or [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "When the made the role call, everybody had to attend with his coat, even though you worked on a construction site with cement and things, which was full of dust.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
